The paper introduces a neural network library aimed at bridging the gap between classic geometric computer vision and deep learning. It proposes new layers that are often used as parametric transformations on the data in geometric computer vision, which can be inserted within a neural network much in the spirit of the original spatial transformers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image processing and manipulation. Additionally, the paper mentions end-to-end learning, which is a common topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed layers can also be used for visual odometry, which falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions unsupervised learning, which is a topic in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with geometric transformations, which is a topic in the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
